wifi: mt76: compat: use kzalloc+struct_size for pre-7.0 kernels

Linux 7.0 introduced kzalloc_flex() and family in commit e4c8b46b924e
("slab: Introduce kmalloc_flex() and family") and adopted them treewide
in commit 69050f8d6d07 ("treewide: Replace kmalloc with kmalloc_obj for
non-scalar types"). mt76/agg-rx.c uses kzalloc_flex() for a flexible-
array struct allocation.

This DKMS package extracts mt76 from the kernel 7.0 tarball but is
compiled against the host kernel, which is commonly 6.1 LTS through
6.19.x. On those hosts the build fails with:

  agg-rx.c: error: call to undeclared function 'kzalloc_flex'

Replace the call with kzalloc(struct_size(...), GFP_KERNEL). struct_size
has existed since kernel 5.x in include/linux/overflow.h. kzalloc_flex
upstream expands to exactly this, so behavior is identical. The call
site is sleepable (regular allocation path), GFP_KERNEL is correct.

Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>

diff --git a/agg-rx.c b/agg-rx.c
--- a/agg-rx.c
+++ b/agg-rx.c
@@ -248,7 +248,7 @@
 
 	mt76_rx_aggr_stop(dev, wcid, tidno);
 
-	tid = kzalloc_flex(*tid, reorder_buf, size);
+	tid = kzalloc(struct_size(tid, reorder_buf, size), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!tid)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
